      "step_index": 1,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Ring systems:** two aromatic rings\n  - Ring A: anisole-like phenyl with **methoxy (\u2013OCH3)** and **chloro** substituent\n  - Ring B: **chloropyridine** (one ring nitrogen; aromatic)\n- **Linker / pharmacophore:** **anilide (amide)**: `Ar\u2013C(=O)\u2013NH\u2013Ar(heteroaryl)`\n- **H-bonding:**\n  - **HBD:** 1 (amide NH)\n  - **HBA:** amide carbonyl O (1), methoxy O (1), pyridine N (1) \u2192 total ~3\n- **Ionizable/basic centers:**\n  - **Pyridine N** is a basic nitrogen but **weakly basic** (pKa typically ~4\u20136 depending on substituents); at pH 7.4 it is mostly unprotonated.\n  - **Amide N is not basic** (resonance-stabilized).\n- **Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition:** lacks **tertiary amine/strongly protonatable center**; no quinidine-like cationic motif.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
